Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees, distributing racks evenly. Slice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges (like steak fries).

Spread @Panko Breadcrumbs{1%cup} on a #baking sheet{}. Toast in oven until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to a large #bowl{} or #shallow dish{}, then add @Parmesan Cheese{1/2%cup} and a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss potatoes, a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @Dried Rosemary{1%teaspoon}, and a large pinch of salt and pepper on same baking sheet. Bake in oven until deeply browned and crisp, ~{25-30%minutes}, flipping halfway through.

Cut @chicken breasts{24%ounce} into 1-inch-wide strips. Season all over with salt and pepper. Crack @eggs{2} into a medium bowl and lightly beat. Working one piece at a time, dip chicken into eggs, letting excess drip off, then coat in panko mixture, pressing to adhere. Place on a lightly oiled baking sheet.

Toss @green beans{12%ounce} on another baking sheet with a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Bake green beans and chicken in oven until chicken is no longer pink in center and green beans are tender and slightly crisp at the edges, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Stir together @Honey{3%ounce} and @Dijon Mustard{8%teaspoon} in a small bowl. Divide chicken, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Serve with honey mustard sauce on the side for dipping.